{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Actually, I come from Britain,"},{"time":3000,"text":"but I've been living in Maldives for 26 years now."},{"time":6000,"text":"So, that's home really."},{"time":8000,"text":"The Maldives, as I'm sure you're aware, are a chain of islands"},{"time":10000,"text":"off the southwest coast of India here."},{"time":12000,"text":"Capital, Malé, where I live."},{"time":14000,"text":"Actually, sitting here today in Mysore,"},{"time":17000,"text":"we're closer to Malé than we are to Delhi, for example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"If you're in IT, India, obviously, is the place to be at the moment."},{"time":24000,"text":"But if you're a marine biologist, Maldives is not such a bad place to be."},{"time":27000,"text":"And it has been my home these years."},{"time":29000,"text":"For those of you who've been there, fantastic coral reefs,"},{"time":31000,"text":"fantastic diving, fantastic snorkeling."},{"time":33000,"text":"I spend as much of my time as possible"},{"time":35000,"text":"investigating the marine life."},{"time":37000,"text":"I study fish,"},{"time":39000,"text":"also the bigger things, whales and dolphins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"This is a blue whale. We have blue whales"},{"time":44000,"text":"in the waters around here, off Maldives,"},{"time":47000,"text":"around the waters of India. You can see them off Kerala."},{"time":49000,"text":"And, in fact, we're very lucky in this region."},{"time":51000,"text":"One of the best places in the world to see blue whales"},{"time":53000,"text":"is here in this region."},{"time":55000,"text":"In Sri Lanka, if you go down to the south coast of Sri Lanka,"},{"time":58000,"text":"during the northeast monsoon season,"},{"time":60000,"text":"you can see blue whales very, very easily."},{"time":62000,"text":"It's probably the best place in the world to see them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"Now, when I talk about the northeast monsoon season,"},{"time":67000,"text":"I'm sure many of you here know exactly what I mean,"},{"time":69000,"text":"but perhaps some of you are not quite so sure."},{"time":72000,"text":"I need to explain a little bit about monsoons."},{"time":74000,"text":"Now, monsoon, the root of the word \"monsoon\""},{"time":76000,"text":"comes from the word \"season.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"So, it's just a season. And there are two seasons in most of South Asia."},{"time":83000,"text":"And in the summer India heats up, gets very hot."},{"time":85000,"text":"Hot air rises, and air is drawn in off the sea to replace it."},{"time":90000,"text":"And the way it works is, it comes from the southwest."},{"time":92000,"text":"It comes off the ocean here and is drawn up towards India."},{"time":95000,"text":"So it comes from the southwest. It's a southwest monsoon."},{"time":98000,"text":"Picks up moisture as it crosses the ocean."},{"time":100000,"text":"That's what brings the monsoon rain."},{"time":102000,"text":"And then in the winter things cool down."},{"time":104000,"text":"High pressure builds over India."},{"time":106000,"text":"And the whole system goes into reverse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"So, the wind is now coming from the northeast"},{"time":111000,"text":"out of India, across the Indian Ocean,"},{"time":113000,"text":"this way towards Africa."},{"time":116000,"text":"Keep that in mind."},{"time":118000,"text":"Now, I'm a marine biologist, but I'm actually"},{"time":120000,"text":"a bit of an old fashioned naturalist, I suppose."},{"time":122000,"text":"I'm interested in all sorts of things, almost everything that moves,"},{"time":124000,"text":"including dragonflies. And I'm actually"},{"time":126000,"text":"going to talk, this afternoon, about dragonflies."},{"time":128000,"text":"This is a very beautiful species, it's called the Oriental Scarlet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"And one thing you need to know about dragonflies,"},{"time":133000,"text":"one important thing,"},{"time":135000,"text":"is that they lay their eggs in fresh water."},{"time":137000,"text":"They need fresh water to breed."},{"time":139000,"text":"They lay the eggs into fresh water."},{"time":141000,"text":"Little larvae hatch out in fresh water."},{"time":143000,"text":"They feed on other little things. They feed on mosquito larvae."},{"time":146000,"text":"So, they're very important."},{"time":148000,"text":"They control mosquito larvae, among other things."},{"time":150000,"text":"And they grow and grow by stages. And they climb out"},{"time":153000,"text":"of the water, burst out, as the adult which we see."},{"time":155000,"text":"And typically, there is a lot of variation,"},{"time":157000,"text":"but if you have a dragonfly with, say, a one year life cycle,"},{"time":160000,"text":"which is quite typical, the larva, living in the fresh water,"},{"time":163000,"text":"lives for 10 or 11 months."},{"time":166000,"text":"And then the adult, which comes after, lives for one or two months."},{"time":169000,"text":"So it's essentially a freshwater animal."},{"time":171000,"text":"It really does need fresh water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"Now, the particular species of dragonfly"},{"time":176000,"text":"I want to talk about is this one,"},{"time":178000,"text":"because most dragonflies, like the one we've just seen,"},{"time":181000,"text":"when the adult is there for its brief one or two months of life,"},{"time":183000,"text":"it doesn't go very far. It can't travel very far."},{"time":186000,"text":"A few kilometers, maybe, is quite typical."},{"time":188000,"text":"They are very good fliers, but they don't go too far."},{"time":191000,"text":"But this guy is an exception."},{"time":193000,"text":"And this is called the Globe Skimmer,"},{"time":195000,"text":"or Wandering Glider."},{"time":197000,"text":"And, as the name might suggest, it is found pretty much around the world."},{"time":200000,"text":"It lives throughout the tropics, the Americas,"},{"time":202000,"text":"Africa, Asia, Australia, into the Pacific."},{"time":205000,"text":"And it wanders far and wide. We know that much about it."},{"time":208000,"text":"But it really hasn't been studied very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"It's a rather mediocre looking dragonfly."},{"time":214000,"text":"If you're going to study dragonflies, you want to study those really bright beautiful ones,"},{"time":217000,"text":"like that red one. Or the really rare ones, the endemic endangered ones."},{"time":220000,"text":"This is, it seems a bit dull you know."},{"time":223000,"text":"It's sort of dull-colored. And it's fairly common."},{"time":226000,"text":"And it occurs everywhere -- you know, why bother?"},{"time":229000,"text":"But if you take that attitude, you're actually missing something rather special."},{"time":232000,"text":"Because this dragonfly has a rather amazing story to tell."},{"time":235000,"text":"And I feel very privileged to have stumbled across it"},{"time":238000,"text":"living in the Maldives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"When I first went to the Maldives,"},{"time":242000,"text":"dead keen on diving, spent as much of my time"},{"time":245000,"text":"as I could in and under the water."},{"time":247000,"text":"Didn't notice any dragonflies; maybe they were there, maybe they weren't."},{"time":249000,"text":"Didn't notice them."},{"time":251000,"text":"But after some time, after some months, one day"},{"time":253000,"text":"as I was going out and about,"},{"time":255000,"text":"suddenly I noticed hundreds of dragonflies, hundreds of dragonflies."},{"time":259000,"text":"Something like this, these are all this species Globe Skimmer."},{"time":262000,"text":"I didn't know at the time, but I know now,"},{"time":264000,"text":"they're Globe Skimmers, hundreds of them."},{"time":266000,"text":"And they were there for some time. And then they were gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"And I didn't think anything more of it until"},{"time":270000,"text":"the following year, when it happened again,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and then the year after that, and then the year after that."},{"time":275000,"text":"And I was a bit slow, I didn't really take too much notice."},{"time":278000,"text":"But I asked some Maldivian friends and colleagues, and yes they come every year."},{"time":280000,"text":"And I asked people about them and yes,"},{"time":282000,"text":"they knew, but they didn't know anything,"},{"time":284000,"text":"where they came from, or anything."},{"time":286000,"text":"And again I didn't think too much of it."},{"time":289000,"text":"But slowly it began to dawn on me that something"},{"time":291000,"text":"rather special was happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"Because dragonflies need fresh water to breed."},{"time":296000,"text":"And the Maldives, and I'm sure some of you have been there --"},{"time":299000,"text":"so here is home."},{"time":301000,"text":"So, Maldives, beautiful place."},{"time":303000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":305000,"text":"It's built entirely of coral reefs."},{"time":307000,"text":"And on top of the coral reefs are sand banks."},{"time":309000,"text":"Average height, about that much above sea level."},{"time":312000,"text":"So, global warming, sea level rise, it's a real serious issue."},{"time":315000,"text":"But I'm not going to talk about that."},{"time":317000,"text":"Another important point of these sand banks"},{"time":319000,"text":"is that when it rains,"},{"time":321000,"text":"the rainwater soaks down into the soil. So, it's gone."},{"time":323000,"text":"So, it stays under the soil."},{"time":325000,"text":"The trees can put their roots into it."},{"time":327000,"text":"Humans can dig holes and make a well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"But dragonflies -- a bit tricky."},{"time":332000,"text":"There is no surface fresh water."},{"time":334000,"text":"There are no ponds, streams, rivers, lakes,"},{"time":336000,"text":"nothing like that."},{"time":338000,"text":"So, why is it that every year"},{"time":340000,"text":"millions of dragonflies, millions,"},{"time":342000,"text":"millions of dragonflies turn up?"},{"time":344000,"text":"I got a little bit curious. In fact I'll stop here,"},{"time":346000,"text":"because I want to ask, and there is a lot of people who,"},{"time":349000,"text":"from India of course, people who grew up spending your childhood here."},{"time":352000,"text":"Those of you who are Indian or spent your childhood here,"},{"time":356000,"text":"let me have a show of hands, who of you --"},{"time":358000,"text":"not yet, not yet!"},{"time":360000,"text":"You're too keen. You're too keen. No. Hang on. Hang on."},{"time":362000,"text":"Wait for the go. I'll say go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"Those of you who grew up in India,"},{"time":369000,"text":"do you remember in your childhood, dragonflies,"},{"time":371000,"text":"swarms of dragonflies? Maybe at school,"},{"time":373000,"text":"maybe tying little bits of string onto them?"},{"time":375000,"text":"Maybe pulling bits off? I'm not asking about that."},{"time":377000,"text":"You've only got to say, do you remember seeing lots of dragonflies."},{"time":381000,"text":"Any hands? Any hands? Yes. Thank you. Thank you."},{"time":384000,"text":"It's a widespread phenomenon"},{"time":386000,"text":"throughout South Asia, including the Maldives."},{"time":390000,"text":"And I got a bit curious about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"In the Maldives -- now, in India there is plenty of water,"},{"time":394000,"text":"so, dragonflies, yeah, of course. Why not?"},{"time":396000,"text":"But in Maldives, no fresh water. So, what on Earth is going on?"},{"time":399000,"text":"And the first thing I did was started recording"},{"time":402000,"text":"when they turned up in the Maldives."},{"time":404000,"text":"And there is the answer, 21st of October."},{"time":406000,"text":"Not every year, that's the average date."},{"time":408000,"text":"So, I've been writing it down for 15 years now."},{"time":410000,"text":"You'd think they're coming from India. It's the closest place."},{"time":412000,"text":"But in October, remember, we're still in southwest monsoon,"},{"time":415000,"text":"Maldives is still in the southwest monsoon."},{"time":417000,"text":"But wind is, invariably, every time, is from the west."},{"time":420000,"text":"It's going towards India, not from India."},{"time":422000,"text":"So, are these things, how are these things getting here?"},{"time":424000,"text":"Are they coming from India against the wind?"},{"time":426000,"text":"Seemed a bit unlikely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428000,"text":"So, next thing I did is I got on the phone."},{"time":430000,"text":"Maldives is a long archipelago."},{"time":432000,"text":"It stretches about 500 miles, of course it's India here."},{"time":434000,"text":"I got on the phone and emailed to friends and colleagues."},{"time":436000,"text":"When do you see the dragonflies appear?"},{"time":439000,"text":"And pretty soon, a picture started emerging."},{"time":441000,"text":"In Bangalore, a colleague there sent me"},{"time":443000,"text":"information for three years, average,"},{"time":445000,"text":"24th of September, so late September."},{"time":447000,"text":"Down in Trivandrum, a bit later."},{"time":449000,"text":"Far north of Maldives, a bit later."},{"time":451000,"text":"Then Malé, then further south."},{"time":453000,"text":"And then the southernmost Maldives."},{"time":455000,"text":"It's pretty obvious, they're coming from India."},{"time":458000,"text":"But they are coming 400 miles across the ocean, against the wind."},{"time":461000,"text":"How on Earth are they doing that?"},{"time":463000,"text":"I didn't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"The next thing I did was I started counting dragonflies."},{"time":467000,"text":"I wanted to know about their seasonality,"},{"time":469000,"text":"what time of year, this is when they first arrive,"},{"time":471000,"text":"but how long are they around for? Does that give any clues?"},{"time":473000,"text":"So, I started a very rigorous scientific process."},{"time":476000,"text":"I had a rigorous scientific transect."},{"time":478000,"text":"I got on my bicycle,"},{"time":480000,"text":"and I cycled around the island of Malé."},{"time":482000,"text":"It's about five kilometers around,"},{"time":484000,"text":"counting the dragonflies as I go,"},{"time":486000,"text":"trying not to bump into people as I'm looking in the trees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"And they're here for a very short time,"},{"time":493000,"text":"October, November, December. That's it."},{"time":495000,"text":"And then they tail off, there's a few, but that's it."},{"time":497000,"text":"October, November, December. That is not the northeast monsoon season."},{"time":499000,"text":"That's not the southwest season."},{"time":501000,"text":"That's the inter-monsoon,"},{"time":503000,"text":"the time when the monsoon changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505000,"text":"Now, what I said was, you get the southwest monsoon going one way,"},{"time":508000,"text":"and then it changes and you get the northeast monsoon going the other way."},{"time":512000,"text":"And that sort of gives the impression you've got one air mass"},{"time":514000,"text":"going up and down, up and down. It doesn't work like that."},{"time":516000,"text":"What happens, actually, is there is two air masses."},{"time":518000,"text":"And there is a front between them, and the front moves."},{"time":521000,"text":"So, if you've got India here,"},{"time":523000,"text":"when the front is up above India you're into the southwest monsoon."},{"time":525000,"text":"Then the front moves into the northeast monsoon."},{"time":529000,"text":"And that front in the middle is not vertical,"},{"time":531000,"text":"it's at an angle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"So, as it comes over towards Malé"},{"time":535000,"text":"I'm standing in Malé underneath the front."},{"time":538000,"text":"I can be in the southwest monsoon."},{"time":540000,"text":"But the wind above is from the northeast monsoon."},{"time":542000,"text":"So, the dragonflies are actually coming from India on the northeast monsoon,"},{"time":545000,"text":"but at an altitude at 1,000 to 2,000 meters up in the air. Incredible."},{"time":551000,"text":"These little insects, it's the same ones we see out here [in India],"},{"time":554000,"text":"two inches long, five centimeters long,"},{"time":556000,"text":"flying in their millions, 400 miles across the ocean,"},{"time":560000,"text":"at 2,000 meters up. Quite incredible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564000,"text":"So, I was quite pleased with myself. I thought wow, I've tracked this one,"},{"time":567000,"text":"I know how they come here. Then I scratched my head a bit,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and that's okay,"},{"time":571000,"text":"I know how they come here, but why do they come here?"},{"time":574000,"text":"What are millions of dragonflies doing, flying out over the ocean every year"},{"time":579000,"text":"to their apparent doom?"},{"time":581000,"text":"It doesn't make sense. There is nothing for them in Maldives."},{"time":583000,"text":"What on Earth are they doing?"},{"time":585000,"text":"Well, to cut a long story short,"},{"time":588000,"text":"they're actually flying right across the ocean."},{"time":591000,"text":"They're making it all the way across to East Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594000,"text":"I know that because I have friends who work on fisheries' research vessels"},{"time":597000,"text":"who have sent to me reports from boats out in the ocean."},{"time":599000,"text":"I know because we have reports from Seychelles,"},{"time":601000,"text":"which fit in as well, down here."},{"time":603000,"text":"And I know because"},{"time":606000,"text":"when you look at the rainfall,"},{"time":608000,"text":"these particular insects, these Globe Skimmers"},{"time":610000,"text":"breed in temporary rain water pools."},{"time":614000,"text":"Okay, they lay their eggs where the seasonal rains are,"},{"time":616000,"text":"the monsoon rains."},{"time":618000,"text":"The larvae have to develop very quickly."},{"time":621000,"text":"They only take six weeks. Instead of 11 months, they're six weeks."},{"time":623000,"text":"They're up, and they're off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"Now, here we have, in case you can't read at the back,"},{"time":627000,"text":"the top is rainfall for India."},{"time":629000,"text":"And we're starting in June. So this is the monsoon rain."},{"time":632000,"text":"By September, October, it's drying out."},{"time":634000,"text":"Nothing for these dragonflies. There is no more seasonal rain."},{"time":636000,"text":"They've got to go hunting for seasonal rain."},{"time":639000,"text":"And they fly south. As the monsoon withdraws to the south"},{"time":642000,"text":"they come down through Karnataka, into Kerala."},{"time":645000,"text":"And then they run out of land."},{"time":647000,"text":"But they are incredibly good fliers. This particular species,"},{"time":649000,"text":"it can fly for thousands of kilometers."},{"time":651000,"text":"And it just keeps going. And the wind, the northeast wind"},{"time":653000,"text":"swooshes it around and carries it off across the ocean to Africa,"},{"time":657000,"text":"where it's raining."},{"time":660000,"text":"And they are breeding in the rains of Africa."},{"time":662000,"text":"Now, this is southeast Africa. It makes it look like there are sort of"},{"time":664000,"text":"two breeding periods here. It's slightly more complicated than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668000,"text":"What's happening is they are breeding in the monsoon rains here."},{"time":671000,"text":"And the dragonflies you can see today"},{"time":674000,"text":"outside here, on the campus,"},{"time":676000,"text":"are the young of this generation."},{"time":679000,"text":"They hatched out in India."},{"time":681000,"text":"They're looking for somewhere to breed. If it rains here they'll breed."},{"time":684000,"text":"But most of them are going to carry on. And next stop,"},{"time":686000,"text":"perhaps only four or five days away is going to be East Africa."},{"time":689000,"text":"The wind will swoosh them out across here."},{"time":691000,"text":"If they pass the Maldives they might go and have a look,"},{"time":694000,"text":"nothing there, they'll carry on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696000,"text":"Here, here, Kenya, East Africa,"},{"time":701000,"text":"they've actually just come out of a long drought."},{"time":703000,"text":"Just last week the rains broke. The short rains broke"},{"time":706000,"text":"and it's raining there now."},{"time":708000,"text":"And the dragonflies are there. I have reports from my various contacts."},{"time":711000,"text":"The dragonflies are here now. They're breeding there."},{"time":713000,"text":"When those guys, they'll lay their eggs now."},{"time":716000,"text":"They'll hatch out in six weeks. By that time"},{"time":718000,"text":"the seasonal rains have moved on. It's not there, it's down here."},{"time":720000,"text":"They'll fly down here. And the clever thing is"},{"time":722000,"text":"the wind is always converging to where the rain is."},{"time":725000,"text":"The rain occurs, these are summer rains."},{"time":727000,"text":"This is a summer monsoon."},{"time":729000,"text":"The sun is overhead there. Summer rains in southern Africa."},{"time":732000,"text":"The sun is overhead, maximum heating,"},{"time":734000,"text":"maximum evaporation, maximum clouds,"},{"time":736000,"text":"maximum rainfall,"},{"time":738000,"text":"maximum opportunities for reproduction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740000,"text":"Not only that, because you have this convection,"},{"time":744000,"text":"you have this rising of the air"},{"time":746000,"text":"where it's hot, air is drawn in."},{"time":748000,"text":"There's a convergence. So, wherever the rain is falling,"},{"time":751000,"text":"the air is drawn towards it to replace the air that's rising."},{"time":754000,"text":"So, the little fellow that hatches out here,"},{"time":757000,"text":"he gets up into the air, he is automatically carried"},{"time":759000,"text":"to where the rain is falling."},{"time":761000,"text":"Lay their eggs, next generation, they come up,"},{"time":764000,"text":"automatically carried to where the rain is falling."},{"time":766000,"text":"It's now back there. They come out, it's time to come back."},{"time":769000,"text":"So, in four generations, one, two, three,"},{"time":771000,"text":"four and then back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773000,"text":"A complete circuit of the Indian Ocean."},{"time":776000,"text":"This is a circuit of about 16,000 kilometers."},{"time":781000,"text":"16,000 kilometers, four generations, mind you,"},{"time":785000,"text":"for a two inch long insect. It's quite incredible."},{"time":787000,"text":"Those of you from North America"},{"time":789000,"text":"will be familiar with the Monarch butterfly."},{"time":792000,"text":"Which, up until now has had the longest known insect migration."},{"time":795000,"text":"It's only half the length of this one."},{"time":797000,"text":"And this crossing here, of the ocean,"},{"time":799000,"text":"is the only truly regular transoceanic crossing"},{"time":804000,"text":"of any insect."},{"time":806000,"text":"A quite incredible feat."},{"time":808000,"text":"And I only stumbled on this because I was living in Malé,"},{"time":810000,"text":"in Maldives for long enough"},{"time":812000,"text":"for it to percolate into my brain"},{"time":814000,"text":"that something rather special was going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818000,"text":"But dragonflies are not the only creatures that make the crossing."},{"time":820000,"text":"There is more to the story."},{"time":822000,"text":"I'm also interested in birds. And I'm familiar"},{"time":824000,"text":"with this fellow. This is a rather special bird."},{"time":826000,"text":"It's a falcon. It's called the eastern red-footed falcon, obviously."},{"time":829000,"text":"But it's also called the Amur Falcon."},{"time":831000,"text":"And it's called the Amur Falcon"},{"time":833000,"text":"because it breeds in Amurland."},{"time":836000,"text":"Which is an area along the Amur River, which is up here."},{"time":838000,"text":"It's the border, much of it is the border"},{"time":840000,"text":"between China and Russia, up here in the far east."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843000,"text":"So, Siberia, Manchuria."},{"time":845000,"text":"And that's where it breeds."},{"time":847000,"text":"And if you're a falcon it's quite a nice place to be in the summer."},{"time":849000,"text":"But it's a pretty miserable place to be in the winter."},{"time":851000,"text":"It's, well, you can imagine."},{"time":853000,"text":"So, as any sensible bird would do,"},{"time":857000,"text":"he moves south. They move south. The whole population moves south."},{"time":860000,"text":"But then the being sensible stopped."},{"time":862000,"text":"So, now they don't stop here, or even down here."},{"time":864000,"text":"No, they turn across here."},{"time":866000,"text":"They have a little refueling stop in northeastern India."},{"time":870000,"text":"They come to the latitude of about Mumbai or Goa."},{"time":873000,"text":"And then they strike out across the ocean, down to Kenya."},{"time":875000,"text":"And down here, and they winter down here [in southern Africa]."},{"time":878000,"text":"Incredible. This is the most extraordinary migration"},{"time":881000,"text":"of any bird of prey. A quite incredible migration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"And they are not the only one that makes the crossing."},{"time":886000,"text":"They have the most incredible journey, but several make the crossing from India"},{"time":889000,"text":"to Africa. Includes this one, the hobby."},{"time":891000,"text":"This fellow is a very nice bird, this is the Pied cuckoo."},{"time":893000,"text":"Those of you from northern India will be familiar with this."},{"time":895000,"text":"It comes with the monsoons."},{"time":897000,"text":"This time of year they cross back to Africa."},{"time":900000,"text":"And this guy, the roller, a rather beautiful bird."},{"time":902000,"text":"It's known as the Eurasian Roller. In India it occurs in the northwest,"},{"time":905000,"text":"so it's known as the Kashmir Roller."},{"time":908000,"text":"And these birds, what I've done is I've complied all the records,"},{"time":910000,"text":"all the available records of these birds,"},{"time":912000,"text":"put them together, and found out they migrate at exactly the same time"},{"time":914000,"text":"as the dragonflies."},{"time":916000,"text":"They make use of exactly the same winds."},{"time":918000,"text":"They travel at exactly the same time with the same winds"},{"time":920000,"text":"to make the crossing. I know they travel at the same altitude."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923000,"text":"It's known about the Amur Falcon. This guy, unfortunately,"},{"time":925000,"text":"one of these met an unfortunate end."},{"time":927000,"text":"He was flying off the coast of Goa,"},{"time":930000,"text":"21 years ago, 1988. October, 1988."},{"time":933000,"text":"An Indian Navy jet was flying off Goa,"},{"time":935000,"text":"bang! In the middle of the night. Fortunately, a two engine jet"},{"time":938000,"text":"got back to base, and they pulled the remains of one of these [Eurasian Rollers] out."},{"time":941000,"text":"Flying at night over the Indian Ocean 2,424 meters."},{"time":945000,"text":"Same height as the dragonflies go."},{"time":947000,"text":"So, they are using the same winds."},{"time":949000,"text":"And the other thing, the other important factor"},{"time":951000,"text":"for all these birds, all medium sized fellows,"},{"time":954000,"text":"and this includes the next slide as well, which is a bee-eater."},{"time":957000,"text":"Bee-eaters eat bees. This one has a nice blue cheek."},{"time":959000,"text":"It's a Blue-cheeked Bee-eater."},{"time":962000,"text":"And every one of these birds that makes the crossing"},{"time":964000,"text":"from India to East Africa"},{"time":966000,"text":"eats insects, large insects,"},{"time":969000,"text":"the size of dragonflies. Thank you very much."},{"time":972000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}